                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/3479: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stafford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-04T12:00:00-04:40"
                            >September 4, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Your telegram No. 81, September 3, 6 p.m. Law has been passed but not
                    promulgated by President who informs me he is returning it to Congress for
                    amendment. Dunn says in confidence that amendment was proposed by Judge
                        Schoenrich<note n="30" xml:id="d123fn30">Counsel for the Dominican
                        Government.</note> and authorizes President to accept suspension or
                    substantial reduction in sinking fund rate on bonds now outstanding in lieu of
                    $25,000,000 issue if latter is found impossible. Dunn plans to leave on plane
                    Sunday and should be in Washington, Tuesday evening. He will urge President to
                    delay passage and promulgation of amended law until appropriate time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stafford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
